Agile Workflow and Work Breakdown Structure

1. Product Vision & Backlog Definition
   1.1. Define core product goals and scope
       - Exam management, session-guided delivery, behavior monitoring, reporting
       - Role-based access for examiners and examinees
       - PostgreSQL target with SQLite fallback
   1.2. Capture key features from project documentation
       - Frontend: React 18 + Vite, feature-based module architecture, real-time WebSocket monitoring
       - Backend: Django modular monolith, REST + WebSocket, layered core/features/shared/AI
       - AI module: frame processing, detection, scoring, anomaly alerts
   1.3. Create product backlog items
       - Auth & profile management
       - Exam CRUD and question management
       - Session lifecycle, timer, response capture
       - Monitoring frame ingestion and fallback REST endpoint
       - Behavior scoring and alerts
       - Reporting and session analytics
       - Shared utilities, DTOs, validation, base models

2. Agile Iterations (Sprints)
   2.1. Sprint 1: Foundation & Core Platform
       - Setup repo, environment, dependencies, and CI conventions
       - Implement core Django settings, URL routing, ASGI/WGI, and shared utilities
       - Scaffold frontend routing, providers, environment config, and shared UI layout
       - Build user auth and role-based access flow
   2.2. Sprint 2: Exam Management & Session Engine
       - Build exam model, serializers, views, and API endpoints
       - Add question model, management, and exam-detail APIs
       - Implement session model, start/submit/terminate endpoints, and response tracking
       - Create examinee exam-taking page and examiner exam management page
   2.3. Sprint 3: Monitoring & Real-Time Communication
       - Develop monitoring service, WebSocket consumer, and fallback REST frame endpoint
       - Create frontend webcam stream and monitoring dashboard components
       - Implement frame stream event flow and analysis result handling
   2.4. Sprint 4: Behavior Analysis & Reporting
       - Add behavior log model, scoring service, and alert generation
       - Implement report service, session summary endpoints, and export support
       - Build behavior UI components and report viewer pages
   2.5. Sprint 5: Polish, Data, and Deployment Readiness
       - Complete profile management, user settings, and examiner/examinee dashboards
       - Seed database data, finalize frontend shared components, accessibility, and responsive layouts
       - Test end-to-end flows, fix bugs, and prepare production settings

3. Work Breakdown Structure (WBS)
   3.1. Project Initiation
       - Review project scope and documentation
       - Identify major features and architecture layers
       - Define sprint goals and acceptance criteria
   3.2. Backend Architecture
       3.2.1. Core
           - Django settings, environment config, ASGI/WGI, URL routing
           - Permissions, exception handlers, global utilities
       3.2.2. Shared
           - Base repository, service, DTO, mixins, validators
           - Common helpers and constants
       3.2.3. Features
           - Auth: user repository, auth service, actions, API endpoints
           - Exams: exam/question models, services, actions, API
           - Session: session lifecycle, answer submission, logs
           - Monitoring: frame processing, WebSocket consumers, REST fallback
           - Behavior: scoring service, behavior log model, alerts
           - Reports: report generation, API views, analytics
           - Profile: user profile endpoints and update actions
       3.2.4. AI Module
           - Pipeline integration, preprocessing, detection, recognition
           - Interface with monitoring and behavior services
   3.3. Frontend Architecture
       3.3.1. Core Layer
           - Router and protected routes
           - Auth, WebSocket, theme, query providers
           - Environment and API configuration
       3.3.2. Feature Modules
           - Auth: login/register forms, hooks, API client
           - Exams: exam builder, exam list, detail hooks, API client
           - Session: timer, answer sheet, question view, session hooks
           - Monitoring: webcam stream, monitoring panel, alerts, live grid
           - Behavior: score indicators, behavior logs, flag components
           - Dashboard: overview cards, alerts, stats charts
           - Reports: report table, export button, log viewer
           - Profile: profile form, avatar upload, profile hooks
       3.3.3. Shared Layer
           - Common UI components, layout, loading/error states
           - Reusable hooks and utilities, global types
   3.4. Database Design
       - Users, exams, questions, sessions, responses
       - Session logs, behavior logs, alerts
       - Relationships and indexes for core lookup paths
   3.5. Quality & Validation
       - Unit tests for backend feature modules
       - Frontend component and hook tests
       - Integration tests for API and monitoring flow
       - Seed data generation and environment verification

4. Release Planning
   4.1. MVP Release
       - Auth, exam creation, session exam-taking, monitoring UI, basic reports
       - Use SQLite development fallback and seed data support
   4.2. Post-MVP Enhancements
       - Real-time AI behavior analysis accuracy improvements
       - Additional monitoring alerts, posture/gaze detection
       - Reporting exports, admin dashboards, and UX polish

5. Continuous Improvement
   - Review and refine backlog each sprint
   - Validate against project vision and acceptance criteria
   - Track dependencies between backend, frontend, AI, and database layers

